{
    "name": "Scouring Swarm",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Each component of a scouring swarm is a slimy, silver gnat with three hook-like legs, a short spout for spraying acidic digestive compounds, and a long proboscis used to slurp up liquefied food. Alone, it is a mere irritant that rapidly perishes in a breathable atmosphere. But despite having no trace of reproductive biology, when two or more are left alone in an oxygen-free environment with plenty of food to consume, they rapidly multiply into a swarm of several thousand creatures.<br/><br/> The swarm appears as a roiling cloud of glittering silver foam, consuming massive amounts of organic material in minutes. Grays\u2014who are believed to have created these creatures\u2014use canisters full of scouring swarms to erase evidence of their presence, even destroying microscopic traces of DNA."
        }
    ],
